TITLE: These top US chains are reinstating their mask requirements
SUMMARY: Top US retail and food chains have updated their mask policies since the US Centers for Disease Control and Prevention said this week that fully vaccinated people should wear masks indoors in areas with substantial  Covid-19 transmission.

TITLE: Pre-market movers
Two North Carolina men were killed by a train while mourning their brother killed in the same spot
SUMMARY: Two men were mourning the loss of their brother, who had been struck by a light-rail train, when they were also struck and killed by a train in North Carolina.

TITLE: Senate moves toward final vote on massive $1.2 trillion bipartisan infrastructure package
SUMMARY: The Senate will reconvene on Sunday at noon to resume consideration of the massive $1.2 trillion bipartisan infrastructure package.

TITLE: One killed, six injured in shooting at a Houston nightclub
SUMMARY: One person died and six others were injured in a shooting early Sunday morning at an after-hours bar in Houston, according to a statement on social media from Harris County Sheriff Ed Gonzalez.

TITLE: One police officer is dead and another is injured after a traffic stop shooting
SUMMARY: Two Chicago police officers were shot Saturday and brought to a local hospital, officials said.

TITLE: Former GOP congressman to join staff of Jan. 6 committee
SUMMARY: Former Rep. Denver Riggleman is joining the staff of the House select committee investigating the January 6 attack on the US Capitol, the third Republican that House Speaker Nancy Pelosi has added to the panel that GOP leadership has attacked as a partisan endeavor.

TITLE: Analysis: Now what? Texas Democrats have a very hard choice to make
SUMMARY: On Friday at midnight, the Texas legislature's special session -- the one in which Democrats fled the state in order to keep a stringent voting bill from being passed -- will come to a close. On Saturday at noon, the next special session of the legislature will open.

TITLE: Biden administration expected to unveil new Belarus sanctions
SUMMARY: The Biden administration is expected to unveil new Belarus sanctions and a new executive order amid continued crackdowns by the regime of strongman leader Alexander Lukashenko.

TITLE: Biden announces three new ambassador picks, including two top donors
SUMMARY: President Joe Biden announced a new round of ambassador picks on Friday, which includes two top donors to his 2020 presidential campaign.

TITLE: Manchin goes after the Fed on inflation
SUMMARY: Democratic Senator Joe Manchin is taking the Federal Reserve to task over inflation

TITLE: Target will cover 100% of college tuition for its workers
SUMMARY: Target has announced that it will begin paying the college tuition and textbook expenses for its US-based part-time and full-time employees who attend select schools.
